  "issue_number": 495,
  "issue_title": "[perf] extract_facts: early-out preference/identity scans + drop favorite replace allocs (#402)",
  "issue_body": "### Summary\n\nAfter #484, `extract_facts` still runs every identity/preference `extract_pattern` scan and calls `extract_favorite` on **all** utterances \u2014 even when no matching phrase exists. `extract_favorite` also allocates via chained `.replace`, and `extract_remember` re-allocates `to_lowercase()` despite the caller already lowercasing.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```bash\ncd genie-claw\ncargo test -p genie-core --release --test extract_bench -- --ignored --nocapture\n```\n\nCommon utterance (`\"the weather today is nice...\"`) still walks all identity/preference prefix scans.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- Skip identity block when no identity substrings present.\n- Skip preference block when no like/dislike/favorite substrings present.\n- `extract_favorite` uses prefix stripping (no `.replace` allocs); only invoked when `\"favo\"` present.\n- `extract_remember` uses ASCII case-insensitive prefix check (no second `to_lowercase`).\n\nOutput byte-identical to current `main`.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nUnconditional scans + extra allocations on the common no-match path.\n\n### Hardware\n\nNon-Jetson (x86_64 dev) for initial bench; Jetson validation in PR.\n\n### GenieClaw version / commit\n\n`main` @ `72b0b28`\n\n### Additional context\n\nM1 #402 performance bucket \u2014 same hot path as merged #484. PR will include differential tests + ignored microbench extension.",
